sql:
SELECT DISTINCT highest_degree
FROM individuals
WHERE age = 39;

external_knowledge:
- Income categories are defined as either <=50K (fifty thousand or less) or >50K (more than fifty thousand); 
- The percentages of individuals above or below the $50,000 income threshold are calculated separately for each work class and marital status combination; 
- The results are grouped and ordered to facilitate comparison across different work classes and marital statuses.

sql:
SELECT marital_status_id, AVG(age) AS average_age
FROM individuals
GROUP BY marital_status_id;
